headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 41 points and rookie LaMelo Ball had 20 points and 11 rebounds to help the Charlotte Hornets beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 120-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier scores 41 points, Hornets beat Timberwolves 120-114

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 24 points and 18 rebounds, and the New York Knicks cruised to a 109-91 victory over the cold-shooting Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks outmuscle Beal-less Wizards in 109-91 win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 23 points and the San Antonio Spurs capitalized on a dominant finish to the first half to beat Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks 125-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan leads Spurs to strong start, 125-114 win over Hawks

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored a career-high 46 points, Kristaps Porzingis added 36 and the Dallas Mavericks overcame Zion Williamson's career-best 36 points in a 143-130 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Williamson hit career highs as Mavs top Pels 143-130

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 33 points, Lou Williams and Marcus Morris Sr. came up big in the fourth quarter, and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Chicago Bulls 125-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard scores 33 as Clippers beat Bulls 125-106

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 30 points, hitting his seventh 3-pointer with 39 seconds to play after Boston cut a 13-point fourth-quarter lead to three, and the Detroit Pistons held on to beat the Celtics 108-102 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey scores 30, hits 7 3s to lead Pistons past Boston 108-102

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic finished an assist shy of a triple-double, scoring 22 points and grabbing 13 rebounds to help the Denver Nuggets rally for a 97-95 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic helps Nuggets rally to beat Thunder 97-95

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 27 points and 12 rebounds, and the Utah Jazz beat the Milwaukee Bucks 129-115 on Friday night for their sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert, Jazz beat Bucks 129-115 for 6th straight win

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 35 points and LeBron James had 28 points, nine rebounds and eight assists in the Los Angeles Lakers' seventh consecutive victory, 115-105 over the Memphis Grizzlies on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis propels Lakers past Grizz 115-105 for 7th straight win

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. had 26 points and the Portland Trail Blazers handed the Cleveland Cavaliers their sixth straight loss with a 129-110 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent has 26 points, Blazers rout Cavaliers 129-110

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic scored 42 points and matched his career high of six 3-pointers as the Orlando Magic beat the Sacramento Kings 123-112 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic scores 42, Carter-Williams helps Magic beat Kings
